# Git Commands

## Normal Use Case

When committing a feature to remote, cd to the directory enclosing the app and do the following:
```bash
git add .
git commit -m "<commit message>"
git push origin <branch>
```
## Basic Commands

### Repository Setup
```bash
# Clone repository
git clone <repository-url>

# Initialize repository
git init

# Add remote
git remote add origin <repository-url>
```

### Basic Operations
```bash
# Check status
git status

# Add files
git add <file>
git add .

# Commit changes
git commit -m "type(scope): description"

# Push changes
git push origin <branch>

# Pull changes
git pull origin <branch>
```

## Branch Management

### Branch Operations
```bash
# List branches
git branch
git branch -a

# Create branch
git checkout -b <branch-name>

# Switch branch
git checkout <branch-name>

# Delete branch
git branch -d <branch-name>
git branch -D <branch-name>  # Force delete
```

### Branch Updates
```bash
# Update local branch
git fetch origin
git merge origin/<branch>

# Rebase branch
git rebase origin/<branch>

# Push branch
git push origin <branch>
git push -u origin <branch>  # Set upstream
```

## Commit Management

### Commit Operations
```bash
# Amend commit
git commit --amend

# Reset commit
git reset --soft HEAD~1
git reset --hard HEAD~1

# Revert commit
git revert <commit-hash>
```

### Commit History
```bash
# View history
git log
git log --oneline
git log --graph

# View changes
git diff
git diff <commit>
git diff <branch1>..<branch2>
```

## Stash Management

### Stash Operations
```bash
# Save changes
git stash save "description"

# List stashes
git stash list

# Apply stash
git stash apply
git stash pop

# Drop stash
git stash drop
git stash clear
```

## Merge Management

### Merge Operations
```bash
# Merge branch
git merge <branch>

# Abort merge
git merge --abort

# Resolve conflicts
git status  # Check conflicts
# Edit files
git add <resolved-files>
git commit
```

## Tag Management

### Tag Operations
```bash
# Create tag
git tag <tag-name>
git tag -a <tag-name> -m "message"

# List tags
git tag
git tag -l "v1.*"

# Push tags
git push origin <tag-name>
git push origin --tags
```

## Configuration

### Git Config
```bash
# Set user info
git config --global user.name "Name"
git config --global user.email "email"

# Set editor
git config --global core.editor "vim"

# Set aliases
git config --global alias.st status
git config --global alias.co checkout
```

## Best Practices

### Commit Messages
- Use conventional commits
- Be descriptive
- Reference issues
- Keep messages concise
- Use present tense

### Branch Management
- Use feature branches
- Keep branches short-lived
- Regular updates from main
- Clean up old branches
- Follow naming conventions

### Workflow
- Regular commits
- Pull before push
- Review changes
- Test before commit
- Keep history clean

### Security
- Don't commit secrets
- Use .gitignore
- Review sensitive data
- Use SSH keys
- Regular updates
